"1382–1456","1340–Male":"1340–Afdød","1342–Female":"1342–Afdød","1456":"1456","1342":"1342","1362":"1362","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1381":"1381","England":"England"},"nl":{"1362–":"1362–Overleden","1362–Female":"1362–Overleden","1360–Male":"1360–Overleden","1382–1456":"1382–1456","1340–Male":"1340–Overleden","1342–Female":"1342–Overleden","1456":"1456","1342":"1342","1362":"1362","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1381":"1381","England":"England"},"en":{"1362–":"1362–Deceased","1362–Female":"1362–Deceased","1360–Male":"1360–Deceased","1382–1456":"1382–1456","1340–Male":"1340–Deceased","1342–Female":"1342–Deceased","1456":"1456","1342":"1342","1362":"1362","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1381":"1381","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Spenlow","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Spendlove  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Spendley","meanings":["English: variant of   Spendlow  ,  see  Spendlove  . For the change in pronunciation compare Henry Spendelowe, 1309 in   Subsidy Rolls   (Beds) with William Spendley, 1569, William Spenley, 1575 in   IGI   (Bedford, Beds).   Redmonds, Dictionary of Yorks Surnames   similarly compares Walter Spendeluf, 1415, Walter Spenlowe, 1433 in   York Guild Register  , with Elizabeth Spendlay, 1522 in   York Guild Register  ; and Robert Spendlove, 1301 in   Subsidy Rolls   (Boltby, NR Yorks) with Thomas Spenley, 1557 in   York Registry Wills   (Thornton in Pickering Lythe, NR Yorks). The name was once particularly common in Lincs, where it mainly occurs as  <i>Spindley</i> in 1881."]},{"name":"Spendlove","meanings":["English: nickname presumably for someone who was free with his affections, from Middle English <i>spend(en)</i> ‘(to) spend or squander’ (Old English <i>spend(an)</i>) + <i>love</i> ‘love’ (Old English <i>lufu</i>)."]},{"name":"Spenceley","meanings":["English: probably, as suggested in   Redmonds, Dictionary of Yorks Surnames  , a variant of   Spendley   in which the consonant cluster /ndl/ has become pronounced /nsl/.  <i>Spendley</i> is itself a variant of   Spendlow   alias   Spendlove  . Redmonds provides circumstantial evidence from   York Guild Register  , where Thomas Spensley, (1477) can be compared with Walter Spenlowe (1433) and Elizabeth Spendlay (1522). Further evidence appears in   IGI   data for Oswaldkirk (NR Yorks), where Johanne Spenclay (1547) is possibly identical with John Spenlay (1550), and in   IGI   data for Bishopwearmouth (Durham): Tho. Spenley (1648) and Richard Spencley (1651). The same developments occurred outside N England. Compare Henry Spendelowe, 1309 in   Subsidy Rolls   (Beds) with William Spendley, 1569, Thomas Spenley, 1571, and John Spensly, 1611 in   IGI   (Bedford, Beds)."]}]},{"name":"Eleanor","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ellenor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor  , the result of blending with   Ellen ."]},{"name":"Elenor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]},{"name":"Elinor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eleanor Spenlow was born in 1362, her father, Edward Spenlow II, was 22 and her mother, Eme Blackney, was 20. She married Edward Bestney I in 1381, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1362–":"1362–Surnud","1362–Female":"1362–Surnud","1360–Male":"1360–Surnud","1382–1456":"1382–1456","1340–Male":"1340–Surnud","1342–Female":"1342–Surnud","1456":"1456","1342":"1342","1362":"1362","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1381":"1381","England":"England"},"fi":{"1362–":"1362–Kuollut","1362–Female":"1362–Kuollut","1360–Male":"1360–Kuollut","1382–1456":"1382–1456","1340–Male":"1340–Kuollut","1342–Female":"1342–Kuollut","1456":"1456","1342":"1342","1362":"1362","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1381":"1381","England":"England"},"fr":{"1362–":"1362–Décédée","1362–Female":"1362–Décédée","1360–Male":"1360–Décédé","1382–1456":"1382–1456","1340–Male":"1340–Décédé","1342–Female":"1342–Décédée","1456":"1456","1342":"1342","1362":"1362","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1381":"1381","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Eleanor Spenlow est née en 1362, son père, Edward Spenlow II, avait 22 ans et sa mère, Eme Blackney, avait 20 ans. Elle a épousé Edward Bestney I en 1381, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1362–":"1362–Verstorben","1362–Female":"1362–Verstorben","1360–Male":"1360–Verstorben","1382–1456":"1382–1456","1340–Male":"1340–Verstorben","1342–Female":"1342–Verstorben","1456":"1456","1342":"1342","1362":"1362","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","